          %h2 Welcome to the BBC Capstone Project Homepage!
        %h5 Project Description:
        %p
          The Automatic Generator Battery Backup Charger (or simply
          =succeed "," do
            %b BBC
          as we call it) is a hardware system regulated by an
          =link_to "Adruino Uno", "https://store.arduino.cc/usa/arduino-uno-rev3"
          microcontroller.
          %br
          %br
          The
          %b BBC
          system connects to general purpose generators and monitors the charge of the generator's internal battery voltage. When the generator's internal battery voltage drops below a user specified threshold (
          %i xx.xV ~ 11.5V
          =succeed "," do
            )
          the
          %b BBC
          system activates the starter, for a user specified amount of time (
          %i 2.0s ~ 3.0s
          =succeed "," do
            )
          in an attempt to power on the generator. If the generator successfully starts and the generator's internal battery voltage reaches a separate user specified threshold (
          %i 14.0V ~ xx.xV
          =succeed "," do
            )
          the
          %b BBC
          system powers off the generator and waits for the generator's internal battery voltage to deplete again, then repeats. If the generator fails to power on, the
          %b BBC
          system delays for a user specified amount of time (
          %i xx ~ 30s
          =succeed "," do
            )
          before activating the starter again. The
          %b BBC
          system is only allowed 3 iterations of failed starter attempts in succession before displaying an error and taking appropriate action.
          %br
          %br
          An
          =link_to "Arduino LCD Keypad Shield", "https://www.dfrobot.com/wiki/index.php/Arduino_LCD_KeyPad_Shield_(SKU:_DFR0009)"
          shows live information about the generator's internal battery voltage and allows the user to control the minimum and maximum generator threshold voltages, the between-iteration delay time, and the starter duration upon bootup. If the attached generator does not power on within the alotted amount of starter time and iterations, the
          %b BBC
          system displays an error message (
          %i Starter Failure!
          ), lights up the red LED indicator, and halts itself to be reset. The
          %b BBC
          system reset feature is to help reduce the likelyhood of the starter or generator burning out during operation.
